column1: # TITLE: Migratory Stationary & Temporal Variation Data
# AUTHOR: Alex Burnham and Samantha Alger
# AUTHOR ADDRESS: 121 Holmes Rd. S. Burlington 05403
# OWNERSHIP: Alex Burnham and Samantha Alger
# COLLABORATORS: Alex Burnham, Samantha Alger, Zac Lamas & Leif Richardson
# REPOSITORY: One or more lines for GitHub, Dryad, or permanent web repositories where data set can be accessed

# we collected samples to assay viruses and other parasites from 58 honeybee colonies at 3 different time points divided into 3 treatments (the controls and pre-exposure "exposed" group serve as the temporal varaition and coinfetion data set (Burnham Dissertation))
# VARIABLE DESCRIPTION: One line for each column in the data set stating what it is and what the units of measurement are
# sample_name: Full sample ID (M=migratory, S=Stationary, E=Exposed) and (1,2 & 3 are sampling events)
# ID: just includes the sample number and treatment letter

# Treatment: Migratory=migratory colonies that went to almonds in CA, Stationary= colonies that stayed in North Carolina, Exposed = colonies that were exposed to the Migratory colonies post migration.
# SamplingEvent: Sampling events spread 4 weeks apart
# NosemaChamber1: Nosema counts for the first hemocytometer chamber
# NosemaChamber2: Nosema counts for the second hemocytometer chamber
# QueenStatus : status of the queen for each colony at each time point. (QueenRight=queen present, Queenless=no queen, QueenCellsPresent= unemerged queen cells were found)
# BroodPattern: measure of how dense the brood pattern was in a colony (1=low, 5=high) (categorical 1,2,3,4,5)
# FOB: how many frames of brood were found in the colony (continuous variable)
# ChalkBrood: Presence (1) or absence (0) for chalkbrood (binary)
# AFB: Presence (1) or absence (0) for American Foul Brood (binary)
# EFB: Presence (1) or absence (0) for European Foul Brood (binary)
# PMS: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Parasitic Mite Syndrome (binary)
# SBV: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Sack Brood Virus (binary)
# Snot: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Snot Brood (binary)
# BSB: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Black Shiney Bee (binary)
# DWV: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Deformed Wings (the phenotype) (binary)
# WaxMoth: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Wax Moth (binary)
# SmallBeetle: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Small Hive Beetle (binary)
# Date: Date of the sampling event
# Yard: name of the bee yard (there are 3)
# BeesAlcPulled: number of bees pulled from the alcohol sample for Nosema Counts
# BeesAlcRemain: number of bees left in alcohol after Nosema counts
# TotBees: total bees in the alcohol sample
# dil.factor: the dilution factor for the RNA isloations prior to qPCR (used to normalize viral load)
# BQCVload: genome copies per bee for black queen cell virus (continuous)
# DWVload: genome copies per bee for deformed wing virus (continuous)
# IAPVload: genome copies per bee for Israeli acute paralysis virus (continuous)
# DWVbinary: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Deformed Wing Virus (binary)
# IAPVbinary: Presence (1) or absence (0) for Israeli acute paralysis virus (binary)
# BQCVbinary: Presence (1) or absence (0) Black queen cell virus (binary)
# NosemaLoad: average nosema load per bee
# Varroa: average varroa load per 100 bees
# logDWV: log + 1 transformed virus load for DWV
# logBQCV: log + 1 transformed virus load for BQCV
# DATA TRACK CHANGES LOG (use this section to record any changes to the data set after it is created)
